## Suggestions for the Project instructions themselves

Project instructions outside this audit's scope, but the prompt invited optional thoughts:

- The Project instructions assert "Phase 1c.2 complete (admin tooling + repo foundation cleanup shipped). Phase 1c.3 (admin UI consolidation) is next." Five 1c.3 slices have shipped. Either the instructions need updating, or the instructions are intentionally lagging-but-stable to avoid churn. If the latter, worth saying so explicitly so a fresh agent reading the instructions doesn't assume they're current.
- "Read authoritative docs rather than relying on these instructions for facts" is the right posture but creates a gotcha when the authoritative doc itself is stale (the roadmap case). Worth adding: "When repo docs and these instructions disagree, surface the gap; don't silently pick one."
- The slice pattern description in the instructions is concise. The repo's F-OPS-4 catalogue (six sub-patterns of pre-execution / integration / transactional / taxonomy halts) is richer. Either pointer the instructions at F-OPS-4 or accept that the instructions are a deliberately-simpler cover.
- The "Don't" list mentions "Don't accept silent scope substitution from Lovable without surfacing." That maps directly to F-OPS-4's "stated scope < actual scope" sub-pattern. Cross-referencing strengthens both.

