## Closing self-check

I rated my comprehension Strategic-aware leaning execution-ready. After writing this audit, I'd hold to that: I can plan and review, but for actual execution I'd want one more session reading the source files (NodeEditor.tsx, the edge function, the Cloud Run service) end to end before I trusted my mental model on a destructive change.

The repo is in better shape than most projects I've seen at this stage. The 6-pass cleanup did what it set out to do. The single most important investment to compound those gains is keeping the roadmap honest as 1c.3 ships — that one drift is doing more comprehension damage than any other documentation issue in the repo.
